@yegor256 I have a few questions regarding this task.
1. I'm thinking about introducing a new interface, `ReleaseAsset`, in order to represent each release asset. Now that seems straightforward to me, but I think having `Release` create `ReleaseAsset` seems like the wrong abstraction in terms of consistency with the rest of the API. Shouldn't we should introduce a new class, `ReleaseAssets` which should handle the usual iterate, create (upload in this case), get, edit, delete operations for `ReleaseAsset`? If this is the case, `ReleaseAssets` can be obtained, by introducing a method `Release.assets()`. Also, we'll have to move all puzzles related to release assets from `ReleaseTest` to somewhere else, probably a new class `ReleaseAssetsTest`, because they belong to `ReleaseAssets` and not `Release`. Do you agree, or should we just keep them in `Release` (with corresponding names such as `iterateAssets`, `uploadAsset` etc.)?
2. The [release asset upload operation](http://developer.github.com/v3/repos/releases/#upload-a-release-asset) has a unique endpoint, `upload.github.com` instead of `api.github.com`. I just set the URI of request to something different, which I tried on my machine and was able to perform asset upload operations. The code is something similar to what's below - does it look all right to you?

``` java
    this.entry.uri().set("https://uploads.github.com")
        .path("/repos")
        .path(repo.coordinates().user())
        .path(repo.coordinates().repo())
        .path("/releases")
        .path(String.valueOf(this.release))
        .path("/assets")
        .back();
```
